| Metric | Year 1 | Year 2 | Year 3 | Year 4 | Year 5 |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Conservative Scenario** | | | | | |
| Net Customers (EOY) | 100 | 600 | 1,400 | 2,800 | 5,000 |
| ARR | $20,000 | $120,000 | $280,000 | $560,000 | **$1,000,000** |
| *Triggers:* Significant delays in grid diff parity; strong defense by incumbents; limited marketing reach. |
| **Base Scenario** | | | | | |
| Net Customers (EOY) | 300 | 1,800 | 4,000 | 8,500 | 15,200 |
| ARR | $75,000 | $450,000 | $1,000,000 | $2,125,000 | **$3,800,000** |
| *Triggers:* Successful MVP launch; strong adoption in Mac/Developer segments; achieving grid diff parity by Y3. |
| **Optimistic Scenario** | | | | | |
